); ventral setae on tibiotarsus distinctly spatulate, shorter than on dorsal side.

Body (Fig. 
45
) oval. Pronotum yellow, with posterior margin and exuvial line brown. Meso- and metanotum yellow with median longitudinal brown stripe. First abdominal tergite brown with posterior third yellow; and median longitudinal brown line. Abdominal tergites II–IX yellow, with lateral end and exuvial line on tergites II–V (or VI) brown. Lateral scoli smooth, I–V brown, VI–VII whitish yellow. Sternites yellow. Antenna, mouth parts, prosternum and legs brown. Elytral portions brownish yellow.
